	The |PhdThesis.cls| class is very similar to the |book.cls| one. 
	Indeed |PhdThesis.cls| mainly patches some features of |book.cls| to
	aid in writing a Ph.D. Thesis or a Master Thesis.
	
	The default behavior of most of the provided features can be
	customized.  See section~\ref{sec:customize} for explanations.
	
	The development of this class has evolved during a long period of time,
	mainly driven by the different needs of plenty of people.  I've been
	trying constantly to use define a user interface as omogeneous as
	possible.  Nethertheless lots of discrepancies are still there.  I
	would welcome any suggestion or criticism which can be useful to
	improve the class.

